        <comment>Scrolling ** Remember the LAYOUT size must be greater than the WINDOW size, otherwise there is nowhere to scroll to.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;In the Projects Properties, under the Project Settings set  Window Size width to 1024 and the Window Size height to 768.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;In the Layout Properties set the width to 5000 and the height to 5000 .&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;To Make a HUD Layer  not scroll, in the Layer Properties set the Parallax X Rate to 0% and the   Parallax Y Rate to 0%&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;To make the Tiled Background cover the entire layout. Under its Common properties, Set Position X  to 0 and Position Y to 0, Set Size width to 5000 and Size height to 5000. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You need to set  the Tiled Background to the back. Right-click the Tiled Background and select Order - To Back. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Lock the Background so you don&apos;t keep selecting it by accident. In the Layers Bar click on the background layer to highlight it. Then click on the pad lock. Now you can&apos;t select it any more.  *****  You can unlock Layers by clicking on the pad lock agian.*****&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;For the object/sprite  you want the game to scroll with, go to the Object Properties and add the Behavior ScrollTo. </comment>
